Section.Catchline: Fees of the Department of State.

SectionBody.Text: The fees of the Department of State under this chapter are as follows:

Subsection.Text: For filing original articles of organization, articles of revocation of dissolution, or a foreign limited liability company’s application for a certificate of authority to transact business, $100.

For filing a certificate of merger of limited liability companies or other business entities, $25 per constituent party to the merger, unless a specific fee is required for a party in other applicable law.
For filing an application for reinstatement after an administrative or judicial dissolution or a revocation of authority to transact business, $100.
For filing a certificate designating a registered agent or changing a registered agent, $25.
For filing a registered agent’s statement of resignation from an active limited liability company, $85.
For filing a registered agent’s statement of resignation from a dissolved limited liability company, $25.
For filing a certificate of conversion of a limited liability company, $25.
For filing any other limited liability company document, $25.
For furnishing a certificate of status, $5.
